======================================================================
PART 1: (H, I₃) AS COMPLETE COORDINATE SYSTEM (n≤8)
======================================================================

  H = I(Ω,2) = 1 + 2α₁ + 4α₂      (at n≤8, α₃=0)
  I₃ = I(Ω,3) = 1 + 3α₁ + 9α₂

  Solving:
    3H = 3 + 6α₁ + 12α₂
    2I₃ = 2 + 6α₁ + 18α₂
    2I₃ - 3H = -1 + 6α₂
    α₂ = (2I₃ - 3H + 1) / 6
    α₁ = (H - 1 - 4α₂) / 2

  So (H, I₃) ↔ (α₁, α₂) is a LINEAR bijection!
  Knowing 2 and 3 gives the full independence polynomial.

  n=5 exhaustive verification:
    (H,I₃) → (α₁,α₂) reconstruction: 1024/1024

  n=7 (500 samples):
    (H,I₃) → (α₁,α₂) reconstruction: 500/500

======================================================================
PART 2: 2-ADIC AND 3-ADIC STRUCTURE
======================================================================

  n=5:
    H mod 2: always 1 (Rédei)
    H mod 3: {0: 424, 1: 240, 2: 360}
    H mod 4: {1: 720, 3: 304}
    H mod 6: {1: 240, 3: 424, 5: 360}

  n=7:
    H mod 2: always 1 (Rédei)
    H mod 3: {0: 304, 1: 359, 2: 337}
    H mod 4: {1: 563, 3: 437}
    H mod 6: {1: 359, 3: 304, 5: 337}

